    <p><i>On January 15, 2016, a new regulation, <a href="https://www.retsinformation.dk/Forms/R0710.aspx?id=175520&exp=1" target="_blank">Denmark Order No. 5 of 01.05.2016</a>, restricting N-nitrosamines and establishing labeling requirements for soother and teats entered into force. The previous Order having same subject was repealed by the Environmental Protection Agency of Denmark.</i></p>
    <p>In general, the regulation restricts the sale of soothers and teats that are made of rubber or elastomer containing not more than 10 μg/kg N-nitrosamines or 100 μg/kg nitrosatable substances. Any producer or importer of the products must provide pre-sale evidence of compliance.</p>
