    <p><i>On February 5, 2016, the French government published a notice (<a href="https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000031979523&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id" target="_blank">NOR: EINC1530221V</a>) which provides a reference standards list for Decree No. 99-777 of 9 September 1999 on the prevention of risks related to the use of deckchairs and transatlantic chairs.</i></p>
    <p>This notice superseded the previous notices in 2014 (NOR: EFIC1404040V) having the same subject. The significant change is that new standard NF D 61-062 (December 2015) replaces its previous version, NF D 61-062 (July 2004), for adjustable deckchairs while the other standards remain unchanged.</p>
    <p>To summarize for the notice, three standards are applicable to deckchairs:</p>
